context: Yale is organized into <a0_0><b5_0>fourteen<b5_0/><a0_0/> constituent schools: the original undergraduate college, the Yale Graduate School of Arts and Sciences, and twelve professional schools. While the university is governed by the <a3_0><b8_0>Yale Corporation<b8_0/><a3_0/>, each school's faculty oversees its curriculum and degree programs. In addition to a central campus in <a4_0><b9_0>downtown New Haven<b9_0/><a4_0/>, the University owns athletic facilities in western New Haven, including the Yale Bowl, a campus in West Haven, Connecticut, and forest and nature preserves throughout New England. The university's assets include an endowment valued at <a1_0><b6_0>$25.6 billion<b6_0/><a1_0/> as of September 2015, the second largest of any educational institution.The Yale University Library, serving all constituent schools, holds more than <a2_0><b7_0>15 million<b7_0/><a2_0/> volumes and is the third-largest academic library in the United States.
